Class DList

java.lang.Object
  list.List
      list.DList

public class DList
extends list.List

A DList is a mutable doubly-linked list ADT. Its implementation is circularly-linked and employs a sentinel node at the head of the list. DO NOT CHANGE ANY METHOD PROTOTYPES IN THIS FILE.

Field Detail

head

protected list.DListNode head
(inherited) size is the number of items in the list. head references the sentinel node. Note that the sentinel node does not store an item, and is not included in the count stored by the "size" field. DO NOT CHANGE THE FOLLOWING FIELD DECLARATION.

Method Detail

back

public list.ListNode back()
back() returns the node at the back of this DList. If the DList is empty, return an "invalid" node--a node with the property that any attempt to use it will cause an exception. (The sentinel is "invalid".) DO NOT CHANGE THIS METHOD.

newNode

protected list.DListNode newNode(java.lang.Object item,
                                 DList list,
                                 list.DListNode prev,
                                 list.DListNode next)
newNode() calls the DListNode constructor. Use this method to allocate new DListNodes rather than calling the DListNode constructor directly. That way, only this method need be overridden if a subclass of DList wants to use a different kind of node.

Parameters:
item - the item to store in the node.
list - the list that owns this node. (null for sentinels.)
prev - the node previous to this node.
next - the node following this node.
